\par \pard\plain \s6\li360\sa31 \f2\fs16 The object of Pegged is to finish the game with only one peg remaining on the board.  The following section explains how to play the game.
\par \pard \s6\li360\sa31 
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Choose a Board Type:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Options menu, choose Cross, Plus, Fireplace, Up Arrow, Pyramid, Diamond, or Solitaire.  Each board presents a different, challenging peg configuration.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Start a New Game:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Game menu, choose New, or press {\fs12 F2}.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Jump a Peg:
\par \pard\plain \s14\fi-360\li720\sa43\tx720 \f2\fs16 1\tab Point to the peg you want to jump with.
\par 2\tab Drag that peg over another peg.
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \tab The "jumped" peg disappears.
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 {\cf6 Note:}  Only certain jumps are legal.  See "Rules of the Game" for more information.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Back Up a Move:
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Game menu, choose Backup, or press the BACKSPACE key.
