\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 Pegged Rules:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc bull.bmp\}\tab The playing area is a plus-shaped grid of holes.  At the beginning of each game, there is a configuration of pegs in the playing area.
\par \pard \s7\li360\sa180\tx360 \{bml hole.bmp\}  A hole
\par \{bml peg.bmp\}  A peg
\par \pard \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \{bmc bull.bmp\}\tab You can remove a peg by jumping over it with another peg.  Only certain jumps are legal:  you must jump horizontally or vertically, and you can jump only one peg at a time.
\par \{bmc bull.bmp\}\tab The game is over when no legal jumps are available.  If there is only one peg remaining, you win.
